  "prompt": "How hard is it to be a single mom?",
  "response": "Being a single mom can be challenging in many ways:\n\n1. Financial strain\n- Often managing household expenses on one income\n- Potential childcare costs\n- Balancing work and parenting\n\n2. Emotional challenges\n- Less personal time and support\n- Higher stress levels\n- Potential feelings of isolation\n\n3. Time management\n- Handling all parenting and household responsibilities alone\n- Limited time for self-care\n- Difficulty balancing work and family\n\n4. Practical difficulties\n- Sole responsibility for childcare\n- No partner to share daily tasks\n- Potential lack of backup support\n\n5. Social and personal life\n- Less opportunity for dating or socializing\n- Limited personal time\n- Potential judgment from society\n\n6. Child-rearing challenges\n- Being the sole role model\n- Managing discipline alone\n- Providing emotional support single-handedly\n\n7. Physical exhaustion\n- Managing multiple roles simultaneously\n- Limited rest and recovery time\n- Potential lack of sleep\n\nDespite challenges, many single moms successfully raise happy, healthy children through resilience, support networks, and determination. Individual experiences vary based on personal circumstances, support systems, and resources.",
